         ✔ 8-REGRESSION: could not create a lobby @done(26-07-18) (FIXED + confirmed in game.
                   Symptom: server select rendered raw codes, status stuck on "connecting"; disabling
                   the mod fixed it. Bisected to bd4c6f2 (8-A) — 6dd9462 good, and the commit between
                   them (1b51472) touched only TODO, so 8-A was the first functional change. Cause:
                   ForgeNetSync.Init() called PhotonNetwork.AddCallbackTarget from BepInEx plugin
                   Awake, which runs before the game's own Photon setup ("Chainloader startup
                   complete" precedes "Starting photon connect"). That forces PUN's static init to
                   build the LoadBalancingClient before ServerSettings are applied. It was the ONLY
                   load-time Photon touch in the mod — every other PhotonNetwork reference sits in
                   gameplay methods. Fix: Init() no longer touches Photon at all; the PUN callback
                   target attaches on VoidManager JoinedRoom/HostCreateRoom and detaches on LeftRoom,
                   idempotent via _registered. VoidManager.Events.Instance was already used at Awake
                   in the known-good build, so it's proven safe there. Logs "[Net] PUN callback target
                   attached/detached" to make the timing visible.
                   LESSON: recorded in CLAUDE.md — never touch PhotonNetwork from Awake.
                   NOTE: this would have been caught by the pending 2-client verification below —
                   worth running T1-T7 before building further on the net layer.)
