                  (Single Harmony postfix on ContextInfoProvider.ContextInfo getter — the call site
                   ContextInfoDisplay uses for BOTH world-hover and held-carryable, so carried and
                   hovered agree for free. Branches on CellModule → BuildBox → relic. Mk maps DIRECTLY
                   onto module level (L3=MkIII vanilla cap … L10=MkX), continuing vanilla's ladder
                   rather than a parallel scale. Header gets the Mk via ForgeLabels.RewriteMark
                   (strip trailing mark, then append); Body gets FORGED block w/ perk names + empty
                   slots + burden names, NO descriptions (vanilla's stat block already shows the real
                   StatMods). Relics get "FORGE TIER: <tier>" — deliberately NOT called rarity, since
                   vanilla's own RarityType is authored separately and includes Epic; vm.Rarity left
                   untouched so rarity colors/sorting elsewhere stay correct. Curse line names the
                   burden with NO odds and NO hedge: only the FIRST cursed relic in a commit
                   contributes, so any per-relic probability would be wrong whenever it isn't first.
                   GATE: only decorates when HasOverlay (level>3 || any perk || any burden) — untouched
                   modules render byte-identical to vanilla, which is ALSO the pre-sync client path,
                   so a desynced client shows vanilla rather than a wrong level. Box state read via
                   ForgeStateStore.TryPeekSnapshot directly, NOT UpgradeForgeBehavior.LevelOfBox —
                   the latter walks the whole UpgradableAssetDataTable, far too expensive for a getter
                   that runs every hover frame. Chose postfix over registering a ContextInfoModifier
                   (the game's own extension point): a modifier would give ContinuousRefreshInterval +
                   DataChanged, but everything shown is fixed at commit time, and injecting one needs
                   reflection into a private [SerializeReference] list plus replaying the Awake-time
                   Init() — which would miss already-awoken objects (late joiners, pre-spawned relics).
                   Fab: RecycleTab.SocketChanged postfix resolves the box via data.logic.RecycleSocket
                   (both hops non-public → AccessTools), scales displayed alloys to match the payout
                   FabricatorRecyclePatch was already applying — a MkX box showed base but paid +105%.
                   Both patches swallow exceptions after one WARN: a throwing hover getter would spam
                   and could break tooltips wholesale. 30 new xunit tests on ForgeLabels, 148 passing.)
